<br>
2. The Role of Network Storage for Data Warehousing<br>
    By Colin White <br>
<br>
This article discusses the issues involved in managing and<br>
administering a high-performance and high-availability<br>
data warehousing and business intelligence system and looks<br>
at the benefits network storage hardware and software offer<br>
in such an environment.<br>
<br>
   <a href="http://www.dmreview.com/d.cfm?E=6231&i=011003&r=2">http://www.dmreview.com/d.cfm?E=6231&i=011003&r=2</a> <br>
<br>
+------------------------------------------------------------+<br>
<br>
3. Super Data Warehousing Solutions<br>
    By Hubert Goodman Jr. <br>
<br>
Successful data warehousing solutions require a strategic<br>
partnership between IT and business. Revisiting lessons<br>
learned and focusing on organizational dynamics are two<br>
ways to achieve super data warehousing solutions.<br>
<br>
   <a href="http://www.dmreview.com/d.cfm?E=6232&i=011003&r=3">http://www.dmreview.com/d.cfm?E=6232&i=011003&r=3</a> <br>
<br>
+------------------------------------------------------------+<br>
<br>
4. On the Marketing Frontier: Collection Time –<br>
&nbsp; The Role of Marketing Revisited<br>
    By Mark Price <br>
<br>
This is the time to evaluate how and what your marketing<br>
department is doing to ensure careful allocation of scarce<br>
resources and to integrate customer insight into the<br>
department to create consistent revenue.<br>
<br>
   <a href="http://www.dmreview.com/d.cfm?E=6234&i=011003&r=4">http://www.dmreview.com/d.cfm?E=6234&i=011003&r=4</a> <br>
